
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Person {
    +firstName: String
    +lastName: String
    +birthDate: Date
}

class Center {
    +name: String (unique)
    +address: String
}

class Room {
    +number: Integer
    +maxCapacity: Integer
}

class Session {
    +date: Date
    +startTime: Time
}

class GroupSession {
    +type: String
}

class IndividualSession {}

class Trainer {
    +diploma: String
}

class Participant {}

' Associations and relationships

Person <|-- Trainer : is a
Person <|-- Participant : is a

Center "1" *-- "many" Room : has
Room "1" *-- "many" Session : can host

Session <|-- IndividualSession
Session <|-- GroupSession

GroupSession "1" --> "1" Trainer : supervised by
IndividualSession "0..*" --> "1" Participant : attended by
GroupSession "0..*" --> "1" Participant : attended by
GroupSession "0..*" --> "1" Session : is a
IndividualSession "0..*" --> "1" Session : is a

' Note about unique constraints and rules
note right of Person
  - Combination of firstName, lastName, and birthDate is unique.
end note

note right of Session
  - At most one session per room per start time in a center.
  - Sessions can have same date/time in different rooms or centers.
end note

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Person`**: Base class for all people. Attributes include name and birth date.
- **`Trainer` / `Participant`**: Specializations of `Person`. A person can be both a trainer and participant.
- **`Center` / `Room`**: Centers contain rooms. Rooms have a number and capacity.
- **`Session`**: Abstract base class with date and start time.
- **`IndividualSession` / `GroupSession`**: Two types of sessions. Only group sessions require a trainer.
- **Relationships**:
  - A `Room` hosts multiple `Session`s.
  - A `GroupSession` has exactly one `Trainer`.
  - A `Session` can have many `Participants`.

